320.7	Radio	Radio	Radio is the transmission of signals through free space by electromagnetic waves with frequencies significantly below visible light, in the radio frequency range, from about 3 kHz to 300 GHz. These waves are called radio waves. Electromagnetic radiation travels by means of oscillating electromagnetic fields that pass through the air and the vacuum of space.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/The_PVR.jpg/250px-The_PVR.jpg
